'''華盛頓地鐵藍線'''（{{lang-en|Blue Line}}）是[[華盛頓都會區捷運系統|華盛頓都會區捷運系統]]的一條路線。蓝线共有27个[[地铁站|车站]]，连接了[[弗吉尼亚州|弗吉尼亚州]]的[[費爾法克斯郡_(維吉尼亞州)|費爾法克斯郡]]、[[亞歷山卓_(維吉尼亞州)|亞歷山卓市]]、[[阿靈頓縣_(維吉尼亞州)|阿靈頓縣]]，[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿哥伦比亚特区]]，以及[[马里兰州|马里兰州]]的[[喬治王子縣|喬治王子縣]]。蓝线的起讫站为[[法兰克尼亚-春田站|法兰克尼亚-春田]]和{{tsl|en|Largo Town Center station|拉戈鎮中心站|拉戈鎮中心}}。蓝线与[[華盛頓地鐵橙線|橙線]]共用13座车站、与[[华盛顿地铁银线|银线]]共用18座车站、与[[華盛頓地鐵黃線|黃線]]共用6个车站；此外，僅有三個車站由蓝线单独使用：[[阿靈頓公墓站|阿灵顿公墓]]、{{tsl|en|Van Dorn Street|梵东街站|梵东街}}和[[法兰克尼亚-春田站|法兰克尼亚-春田]]。

== 历史 ==
[[File:Reagan_National_Metro_Station.jpg|thumb]]]]
在华盛顿都会区兴建地铁的计划起始于1955年的大运量交通调查，这项调查旨在预估高速公路和大运量公共交通系统到1980年的运量需求。<ref>Schrag at p. 33-38.</ref>这项研究在1959年的最终报告中包含了两条快速公共交通线路，其在华盛顿城内的形式预计为地铁。<ref>Schrag at p. 39.</ref>由于这项计划同时需要在华盛顿特区大量兴建高速公路，当地居民游说联邦立法者建立一份高速公路修建的备忘录，直到1962年7月1日。<ref>Schrag at p. 42.</ref>{{tsl|en|National Capital Transportation Agency|国家首都运输局}}在1962年一份名为《国家首都区域的交通》的报告中提出了一条与现今蓝线在弗吉尼亚的线路基本相同的路线：沿着阿灵顿到亚历山卓和春田的既有铁路修建。<ref name="Schrag at p. 55">Schrag at p. 55.</ref>报告中没有提及乔治王子郡境内的线路。<ref name="Schrag at p. 55"/>直到[[华盛顿都会区交通局|华盛顿都会区交通局]]（缩写：{{lang|en|WMATA}}）成立，这条线路都被保留在快速公共交通计划中。

1966年10月WMATA成立后，公共交通系统的计划工作从联邦转移到这个由特区、马里兰州和弗吉尼亚州代表组成的地区机构；项目的兴建不再需要担忧[[美国国会|国会]]的批准与否。<ref>Schrag at p. 104</ref>相反，规划的线路需要服务以上三个地区来保证它们会批准这个系统运转所需的经费。<ref>Schrag at p. 108</ref>

蓝线在弗吉尼亚的部分于今天的线路基本相同，即沿着{{tsl|en|Richmond, Fredericksburg and Potomac Railroad|里士满、弗雷德里克斯堡和波多马克铁路}}（[[宾夕法尼亚铁路|宾州铁路]]的子公司）到{{tsl|en|Colchester, Virginia|科尔切斯特 (弗吉尼亚州)|科尔切斯特}}段的线路修建，因为沿着既有铁路修建是在城郊修建时最便宜的选择。<ref>Schrag at p. 110-11.</ref>蓝线在地面另有一段线路沿着{{tsl|en|Virginia State Route 110|110号弗吉尼亚州级公路}}修建，它路过[[阿灵顿国家公墓|阿灵顿国家公墓]]、连接[[五角大楼|五角大楼]]和{{tsl|en|Rosslyn, Virginia|罗斯林 (弗吉尼亚州)|罗斯林}}，并取代了一段当时已关闭的罗斯林接驳铁路（{{lang-en|Rosslyn Connecting Railroad}}，也是宾州铁路的子公司）。<ref>(1) {{cite web|author=Frank IBC|title=Comments|work=The Metro plan has changed a lot since 1968|publisher=Greater Greater Washington|date=2014-07-26|url=https://ggwash.org/view/35475/the-metro-plan-has-changed-a-lot-since-1968|quote=There used to be a rail line from Rosslyn to the Long Bridge, but that was replaced by the Blue Line.|access-date=June 28, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170628175917/https://ggwash.org/view/35475/the-metro-plan-has-changed-a-lot-since-1968|archive-date=2017-06-28}}<br />(2) 1942 map showing the Rosslyn Connecting Railroad, the planned route of Virginia State Route 110 (below the railroad), The Pentagon building and Arlington National Cemetery: {{cite web|url=http://www.historicmapworks.com/Map/US/895526/Plate+022/Arlington+County+1943/Virginia/|title=Plate 22|work=Plat Book of Arlington County, Virginia|year=1943|location=Philadelphia, Pennsylvania|publisher=Franklin Survey Company|via=Historic Map Works, LLC. Residential Genealogy|access-date=2019-10-25|archive-date=2021-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210825041043/http://www.historicmapworks.com/Map/US/895526/Plate+022/Arlington+County+1943/Virginia/|dead-url=no}}<br />(3) Maps and images of the area near the former route of the Rosslyn Connecting Railroad at the Arlington Cemetery Station of Metrorail's Blue Line (Coordinates: {{coord|38.884224|-77.062888|region:US_type:landmark_scale:7500_source:wikimapia|format=dms|name=Arlington Cemetery Station of Metrorail's Blue Line in Arlington County, Virginia}})</ref>
<ref name=Connecting>(1) {{cite web|url=http://scripophily.net/rocoracovi19.html|title=Certificate: Rosslyn Connecting Railroad Company - Virginia 1944|publisher=Scripophily.com|access-date=2017-06-27|quote=Continuing south in Virginia was the Alexandria and Washington Railroad, opened in 1857. The Baltimore and Potomac acquired this line after reaching it, operating it until 1901, when the Washington Southern Railway (the successor of the Alexandria and Washington) was taken over by the Richmond, Fredericksburg and Potomac Railroad, an independent bridge line owned equally by the PRR and five other railroads. Soon after, in 1904, the line from the Long Bridge to Rosslyn, built by the Washington Southern, was split off into the Rosslyn Connecting Railroad, owned by the PRR.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170628175640/http://scripophily.net/rocoracovi19.html|archive-date=2017-06-28}}<br />(2) {{cite web|date=2003-07-26|title=Re: W&OD Railroad - Adjacent to Pentagon?|author=CSXvet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701184025/https://www.trainorders.com/discussion/read.php?11,593894|archive-date=2017-07-01|url=https://www.trainorders.com/discussion/read.php?11,593894|work=Nostalgia & History > W&OD Railroad|publisher=Trainorders.com|via=Digicert.com|access-date=2017-07-01|quote=The railroad that ran past the Pentagon was the onetime Pennsylvania RR Rosslyn branch. This branch left the mainline at RO (for Rosslyn) tower at the south end of the bridge over the Potomac and basically followed the Potomac northwest to Rosslyn. Part of it was built on the bed of the old canal that connected Alexandria with the C&O Canal in Georgetown.}}<br />(3) {{cite journal|author=The Commission|url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015024015458&view=1up&seq=778|title=Valuation Docket No. 160: Rosslyn Connecting Railroad Company: Appendix 1|journal=Interstate Commerce Commission Reports: Decisions of the Interstate Commerce Commission of the United States (Valuation Reports): October 1925 — February 1926|volume=106|location=Washington, D.C.|publisher=United States Government Publishing Office|year=1926|page=678|issn=0083-1530|oclc=6392128|via=HathiTrust Digital Library|access-date=2019-10-26|quote=The grading is rather light. The most of the line follows along the route of an old disused canal and in constructing the roadbed the carrier used the canal grading as far as possible.|archive-date=2021-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210825050203/https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015024015458&view=1up&seq=778|dead-url=no}}</ref>这个铁路公司的前身，{{tsl|en|Washington Southern Railway|华盛顿南方铁路}}在1896年兴建了这段铁路，并利用了当时已废弃的{{tsl|en|Alexandria Canal (Virginia)|亚历山卓运河}}。<ref name=Connecting/><ref>(1) {{cite book|last=Wilson|first=William Bender|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qj9N-eWi71YC&pg=PA332|page=332|title=History of the Pennsylvania Railroad Company: with Plan of Organization, Portraits of Officials and Biographical Sketches|volume=1|location=Philadelphia|publisher=Henry T. Coates & Co.|year=1899|oclc=671596804|access-date=2017-06-27|via=[[Google_Books|Google Books]]|quote=The Washington Southern Railway extends from the junction of the Baltimore and Potomac Railroad at the south end of the Long Bridge, opposite Washington, D. C., to Quantico, Virginia, a distance of 32.12 miles.  It has three branches — .... ; and the Rosslyn branch from the south end of the Long Bridge to the south end of the Aqueduct at the village of Rosslyn, Va., opposite Georgetown, D. C., a distance of 1.13 miles. This latter branch was opened for business April 2, 1896.|archive-date=2021-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210825041042/https://books.google.com/books?id=qj9N-eWi71YC&pg=PA332|dead-url=no}}<br />(2) 1900 map showing the Washington Southern Division of the Pennsylvania Railroad (formerly the Washington Southern Railway) inside the route of the "Old Alexandria Canal" within the "Arlington Reservation", between the Potomac River and the "National Cemetery": {{cite web|url=https://www.loc.gov/resource/g3883a.ct002287/?r=0.331,0.593,0.562,0.272,0|title=Map of Alexandria County, Virginia for the Virginia Title Co.|year=1900|location=Alexandria, Virginia|publisher=The Company|access-date=2019-10-07|via=Library of Congress website|archive-date=2021-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210825045905/https://www.loc.gov/resource/g3883a.ct002287/?r=0.331,0.593,0.562,0.272,0|dead-url=no}}</ref>

1968年3月，WMATA委员会批准了一项总长{{convert|98|mi|km|}}的“采用的区域系统”（{{lang-en|Adopted Regional System}}，缩写：ARS），其中包含蓝线亨廷顿到艾迪逊路的部分，并保留了路线延伸到拉戈的可能性。<ref>Schrag at p. 117.</ref>ARS中也包含蓝线、[[华盛顿地铁橙线|橙线]]在俄克拉荷马大道的位于体育场、军械库和阿纳卡斯蒂亚河大桥之间的一个车站。当地居民反对车站附带的一个1,000车位的[[停车换乘|停车场]]以及它可能带来的交通流量。作为回应，特区政府要求移除这个车站，并使线路的地下通道延伸穿过这个社区。<ref>Schrag at p. 161.</ref>这也是蓝线唯一一个由于居民反对而取消的车站。<ref name="June 12, 1977">{{Citation |last =Gorney|first=Cynthia |title =Neighbors' unity wins fight against Metro station |newspaper =The Washington Post |page =C1 |date =1977-06-12}}</ref>这个取消的地上站和停车场节省了1,200万美元的资金，线路也应居民要求轻微调整了线路走向。<ref name="June 12, 1977"/>为了更好地服务游客，史密森尼学会的车站新增了一个在[[国家广场|国家广场]]的出站口；此外，联邦政府在1972年要求蓝线在[[阿灵顿公墓|阿灵顿公墓]]新增一个[[阿灵顿公墓站|车站]]。联邦政府支付了这两处设计变更产生的花费。<ref>Schrag at p. 254.</ref>

[[File:Addison_Road-Seat_Pleasant_Station.jpg|thumb]]
蓝线于1977年7月1日正式开始运营，共开通从[[阿灵顿县_(弗吉尼亚州)|阿灵顿]]的[[罗纳德·里根华盛顿国家机场站|罗纳德·里根华盛顿国家机场]]到华盛顿特区的[[体育场-军械库站|体育场-军械库]]共计18个车站；这是华盛顿地铁第一条通往[[弗吉尼亚州|弗吉尼亚州]]的线路。<ref name="July 1, 1977">{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/washingtonpost_historical/doc/146696896.html|last=Feaver|first=Douglas B.|title=Today, Metro could be U.S. model|newspaper=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|page=A1|date=1977-07-01|quote=With the opening today of its 12-mile-long Blue Line from National Airport to RFK Stadium, Washington's Metro subway grows from a downtown demonstration line into the spine of a regional transportation system that could rival the Capital Beltway in its effect on Washington.|access-date=2017-07-01|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701225119/https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/washingtonpost_historical/doc/146696896.html|archive-date=2017-07-01}}</ref><ref name=History1>{{cite web|url=https://www.wmata.com/about/upload/history.pdf|title=Metro History|publisher=Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority|access-date=2017-07-01|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701214349/https://www.wmata.com/about/upload/history.pdf|archive-date=2017-07-01}}</ref>随后，蓝线于1980年11月22日延伸了3个车站到{{tsl|en|Addison Road (WMATA station)|艾迪逊路站|艾迪逊路}}。<ref name="November 23, 1980">{{cite news |last =Cooke |first =Janet |title =Three new Metro stations have a festive first day |newspaper =The Washington Post |page =D1 |date =1980-11-23}}</ref>随着{{tsl|en|Van Dorn Street (WMATA station)|梵东街站}}于1991年6月15日投入使用，蓝线在国家机场以南的服务也得到延伸。<ref name="June 15, 1991">{{cite news |last =Staff Reporters |title =Van Dorn Station to open |newspaper =The Washington Post |page =B5 |date =1991-06-15}}</ref> 1997年6月29日，[[法兰克尼亚-春田站|法兰克尼亚-春田站]]开通，蓝线原有的计划到此时已全部完成。<ref name="June 27, 1997">{{cite news |last =Tousignant |first =Marylou |title =At last, Metro reaches end of the Blue Line; Franconia-Springfield station to begin service on Sunday |newspaper =The Washington Post |page =B1 |date =1997-06-27}}</ref>2004年12月18日，两个位于[[马里兰州|马里兰州]]的车站：{{tsl|en|Morgan Boulevard (WMATA station)|摩根大道站}}和{{tsl|en|Largo Town Center (WMATA station)|拉戈镇中心站}}也投入使用。<ref name="December 19, 2004">{{cite news |last =Dana |first =Rebecca |title =Metro, Prince George's extend their reach; Two new Blue Line stations open, bringing passengers and economic potential |newspaper=The Washington Post |page =C2 |date =2004-12-19}}</ref>

橙线自从1978年11月20日开通到1979年12月1日，都和蓝线在国家机场站到体育场-军械库站之间和蓝线共线。在体育场-军械库站之后，橙线单独向东驶往[[新卡罗顿站|新卡罗顿]]。<ref name="November 18, 1978">{{cite news |last=Eisen |first =Jack |author2=John Feinstein |title =City-County fanfare opens Orange Line; Ceremonies open new Orange Line|newspaper=The Washington Post |page = D1 |date =1978-11-08}}</ref>1979年12月1日起，橙线向西从[[罗斯林站|罗斯林]]和蓝线分开，终到站为{{tsl|en|Ballston–MU (WMATA station)|巴尔斯顿-马利蒙特大学站|巴尔斯顿-马利蒙特大学}}。<ref name="December 2, 1979">{{cite news |last = Feaver |first = Douglas B. |author2=Sandra G. Boodman |title = Area celebrates extension of Metrorail in Arlington |newspaper = The Washington Post |page = C1 |date =1979-12-02}}</ref>蓝线和橙线仍然在罗斯林到体育场-军械库之间共线；[[华盛顿地铁银线|银线]]也在同一区间共线。<ref name="Silver">{{cite web|url=http://www.dullesmetro.com/about/overview.cfm |title=Dulles Metrorail Project Overview |author=Metropolitan Washington Airports Authority |year=2010 |access-date= 2010-07-25 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100727163238/http://www.dullesmetro.com/about/overview.cfm |archive-date=2010-07-27 }}</ref>

[[File:Farragut_West_station.jpg|thumb]]]]
蓝线最初的规划与现在的线路稍有不同。原计划是蓝线驶往{{tsl|en|Huntington (WMATA station)|亨廷顿站|亨廷顿}}，而[[华盛顿地铁黄线|黄线]]驶往法兰克尼亚-春田。更改这一计划的原因是到亨廷顿的线路修建完成时，车卡数量短缺。由于黄线线路更短，运营所需的车卡数量比蓝线更少，所以两线的终点站发生了交换。<ref name="March 16, 1990">{{Citation |last =Henderson |first=Nell |title =Metro seeks comments on budget that includes new rail stations |newspaper =The Washington Post |page =D3 |date =1990-03-16}}</ref>1999年到2008年间，蓝线在[[美国独立日|独立日]]执行特别运行图，7月4日的终点站会改为亨廷顿。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://transit.schuminweb.com/transit/wmata/miscellaneous.php?category=july-4-service |title=July 4 Service |author=The Schumin Web Transit Center |access-date=2010-07-26 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110524184945/http://transit.schuminweb.com/transit/wmata/miscellaneous.php?category=july-4-service |archive-date=2011-05-24}}</ref>

在ARS的计划里，蓝线的终点站是艾迪逊路。然而体育观众一直要求将地铁再延伸{{convert|3|mi}}到位于[[拉戈_(马里兰州)|拉戈]]的{{tsl|en|Capital Centre (Landover, Maryland)|首都中心 (马里兰州)|首都中心}}体育馆。1997年2月27日，WMATA委员会批准了延长线的修建。<ref name=History1/>但到2004年延长线开通运营的时候，职业篮球、曲棍球的场馆已经移动到了[[画廊站|画廊站]]附近的[[第一资本竞技馆|新场馆]]，且首都中心处也改建为了购物中心。不过延长线仍然服务了不少体育观众，因为橄榄球的[[联邦快递球场|联邦快递球场]]亦位于延长线的步行距离之内。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wmata.com/rider-guide/events/#FedEx_Field |title=Evens and Venues: FedEx Field |publisher=WMATA |access-date=2018-11-08 |archive-date=2022-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220308142152/https://wmata.com/rider-guide/events/#FedEx_Field |dead-url=no }}</ref>延长线的修建总共花费了4亿5600万美元。<ref name="January 1, 2005">{{cite news |last =Partlow |first =Joshua |title =Newest stations to ease game-day crush; Redskins fans await rail, trail to FedEx |newspaper =The Washington Post |page =B3 |date =2005-01-01}}</ref>

1998年，国会将华盛顿国家机场重命名为罗纳德·里根华盛顿国家机场，更名法案特别说明不为改名划拨经费。因此，WMATA没有更改国家机场站（当时只有“国家机场”而非其更改后的全名）的名字。在国会共和党议员反复要求更改站名后，WMATA表示只有在地方政府的要求下才会更改站名。由于阿灵顿县和哥伦比亚特区都由民主党控制，更名计划一直受阻。直到2001年，国会将车站更名列为继续提供联邦资金的条件后，车站才更改为现在的名字。<ref>Schrag at p. 258.</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=GOP Ups Pressure on Metro|first=Lyndsey|last=Layton|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|date=2001-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=House Votes to Require 'Reagan' at Metro Stop|first=Lyndsey|last=Layton|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|date=2001-12-01}}</ref><ref>''2002 Transportation Appropriations Act'', Public Law 107-87, section 343, Statutes at Large 115 (2001) 833.</ref>

2018年5月，华盛顿地铁宣布了一项涉及20个车站的大规模翻修计划。为了适应站台重修的需要，蓝线和黄线在国家机场站以南的部分在2019年5月到9月间关闭；这是当时华盛顿地铁历史上最长的一次线路关停，两条线路所有列车的终点站都因此改为罗纳德·里根国家机场。<ref>{{cite web | title=Metro wants to rebuild 20 station platforms over three years, creating SafeTrack-like disruptions | website=Washington Post | date=2018-05-07 | url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/trafficandcommuting/metro-wants-to-rebuild-20-station-platforms-in-three-years-creating-safetrack-like-disruptions/2018/05/07/f7c19dcc-5164-11e8-abd8-265bd07a9859_story.html | access-date=2019-02-19 | archive-date=2019-02-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190219072942/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/trafficandcommuting/metro-wants-to-rebuild-20-station-platforms-in-three-years-creating-safetrack-like-disruptions/2018/05/07/f7c19dcc-5164-11e8-abd8-265bd07a9859_story.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=Metro plans 'summer shutdown' on Blue, Yellow lines next year | website=WTOP | date=2018-05-07 | url=https://wtop.com/tracking-metro-24-7/2018/05/metro-plans-summer-shutdown-on-blue-yellow-line-next-year/ | access-date=2019-02-19 | archive-date=2019-02-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190219130135/https://wtop.com/tracking-metro-24-7/2018/05/metro-plans-summer-shutdown-on-blue-yellow-line-next-year/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Metro and regional officials urge customers to finalize alternative travel plans as summer 2019 station closures approach |url=https://www.wmata.com/service/rail/PlatformProject/Metro-and-regional-officials-urge-customers-to-finalize-alternative-travel-plans-as-summer-2019-station-closures-approach.cfm |website=www.wmata.com |publisher=Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority |access-date=2020-03-06 |date=2019-05-22 |archive-date=2021-08-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210825234130/https://www.wmata.com/service/rail/PlatformProject/Metro-and-regional-officials-urge-customers-to-finalize-alternative-travel-plans-as-summer-2019-station-closures-approach.cfm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Metro stations on Blue/Yellow lines to reopen Monday as planned |url=https://www.wmata.com/service/rail/PlatformProject/return-to-service.cfm |website=www.wmata.com |publisher=Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority |access-date=2020-03-06 |date=2019-09-07 |archive-date=2021-08-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210825233229/https://www.wmata.com/service/rail/PlatformProject/return-to-service.cfm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

由于受到[[2019冠状病毒病美国疫情|2019冠状病毒病疫情]]影响，在2020年3月26日到6月28日间，列车经过{{tsl|en|Van Dorn Street station|梵东街站}}、[[阿灵顿公墓站|阿灵顿公墓站]]、[[联邦三角站|联邦三角站]]、[[史密森尼站|史密森尼站]]、[[联邦中心西南区站|联邦中心西南区站]]和{{tsl|en|Morgan Boulevard station|摩根大道站}}时不停靠。<ref name=covidmap>{{cite web |url=https://www.wmata.com/schedules/maps/upload/2019-System-Map-COVID-19-stations-FINAL.pdf |title=Special Covid-19 System Map |publisher=Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority |access-date=2020-04-14 |archive-date=2020-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327192846/https://www.wmata.com/schedules/maps/upload/2019-System-Map-COVID-19-stations-FINAL.pdf |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name=covidservice>{{cite web |url=https://www.wmata.com/service/status/details/covid-station-closures.cfm |title=Metrorail stations closed due to COVID-19 pandemic |date=2020-03-23 |publisher=Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority |access-date=2020-04-14 |archive-date=2021-08-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210825234252/https://www.wmata.com/service/status/details/covid-station-closures.cfm |dead-url=no }}</ref>除阿灵顿公墓站外的所有车站于2020年6月28日重新开启运作。<ref>{{cite web |title=Metro to reopen 15 stations, reallocate bus service to address crowding, starting Sunday {{!}} WMATA |url=https://www.wmata.com/about/news/Metro-to-reopen-15-stations-reallocate-bus-service.cfm |website=www.wmata.com |access-date=2020-06-22 |archive-date=2021-12-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211217080714/https://www.wmata.com/about/news/Metro-to-reopen-15-stations-reallocate-bus-service.cfm |dead-url=no }}</ref>阿灵顿公墓站则于之后的2020年8月23日恢复服务。<ref>{{cite web |title=Metro announces reopening of East Falls Church and Arlington Cemetery stations on Aug. 23 |url=https://wjla.com/news/metro-summer-shutdown/metro-announces-reopening-of-east-falls-church-and-arlington-cemetery-stations |website=WJLA |access-date=2020-08-23 |date=2020-08-17 |archive-date=2021-08-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210825231708/https://wjla.com/news/metro-summer-shutdown/metro-announces-reopening-of-east-falls-church-and-arlington-cemetery-stations |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2020年11月27日到2021年3月14日，由于亚历山卓车辆段（{{lang|en|Alexandria Rail Yard}}）信号系统现代化工程影响，[[法兰克尼亚-春田站|法兰克尼亚-春田站]]和梵东街站关闭，蓝线在周末大多会转而运营亨廷顿站和{{tsl|en|Eisenhower Avenue station|艾森豪威尔大道站}}。此外，2020年12月20日到2021年1月3日，亚历山卓车辆段完全关闭期间，蓝线也改为运行至亨廷顿站。华盛顿地铁选择全段关闭而非保留[[单线铁路|单线运营]]，是因为这样会使工期翻倍，且使用单线运营会使列车间隔延长至36分钟一班。<ref>{{cite web |title=Metro to advance safety-critical work on Blue Line during historically low ridership {{!}} WMATA |url=https://www.wmata.com/about/news/Metro-to-advance-safety-critical-work-on-Blue-Line.cfm |website=www.wmata.com |access-date=2020-11-14 |archive-date=2021-03-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210321124957/https://www.wmata.com/about/news/Metro-to-advance-safety-critical-work-on-Blue-Line.cfm |dead-url=no }}</ref> 

2020年12月14日，WMATA宣布蓝线将在2021年2月13日到5月23日期间停驶，以完成阿灵顿公墓站和艾迪逊路站的改造。此外，[[华盛顿地铁黄线|黄线]]则会运营法兰克尼亚-春田到{{tsl|en|Mount Vernon Square station|维农山广场站}}区间，而[[华盛顿地铁银线|银线]]会服务蓝线的部分线路。<ref>{{cite web |title=Metro announces travel alternatives during spring platform reconstruction work {{!}} WMATA |url=https://www.wmata.com/about/news/Spring-2021-Platform-Project-Travel-Alternatives.cfm |website=www.wmata.com |access-date=2020-12-15 |archive-date=2021-08-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210825233159/https://www.wmata.com/about/news/Spring-2021-Platform-Project-Travel-Alternatives.cfm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 路线 ==
[[File:Franc-Springd_platform,_inbound_end.jpg|thumb]]]]
华盛顿地铁蓝线于西南方向的终点站是[[法兰克尼亚-春田站|法兰克尼亚-春田站]]，位于前线路（{{lang|en|Frontier Drive}}）和法兰克尼亚-春田公园大道（{{lang|en|Franconia-Springfield Parkway}}，弗吉尼亚289号公路）的路口。蓝线在地面上沿着[[CSX运输|CSX运输]]的铁路向北，并与黄线在亚历山德里亚老城的国王街交汇；共线之后继续沿着CSX铁路向北，直到向东抬高为高架线路，进入国家机场车站。之后蓝线在水晶城的南15街进入地下隧道，向北穿过海耶斯街和五角大楼的停车场。蓝线在这个隧道与黄线分离，并沿着110号弗吉尼亚州级公路在地面向北，然后在罗斯林以南进入地下，并和橙线、银线共线。隧道在地下穿过北林恩街、[[波多马克河|波多马克河]]，然后沿西北区I街向东。隧道在西北区第12街向南，在[[地铁中心站_(华盛顿)|地铁中心站]]从下面穿过红线。隧道在西南区D街下向东转，在[[朗方广场站|朗方广场站]]从下面穿过黄、绿线。隧道继续沿着东南区宾夕法尼亚大道、G街和波多马克大道向东，然后沿着东南区第19街向北、在东北区俄克拉荷马大道附近的[[罗伯特·F·甘迺迪纪念体育场|罗伯特·F·甘迺迪纪念体育场]]转为地面线。蓝线随后经本宁路附近的桥穿过[[安那考斯迪亚河|安那考斯迪亚河]]，与橙线分离并再次进入地下隧道，沿着东国会街穿过本宁路向东。蓝线和银线随后转为地面或高架线（偶尔有较短的隧道）从艾迪逊路站沿着中央大道直到东边的终点站{{tsl|en|Largo Town Center station|拉戈镇中心站}}。<ref name=aaa>{{cite map
 |publisher  = AAA
 |title      = Metro Washington D.C. Beltway
 |edition    = 2000–2001
 |year       = 2000
 |scale      = 1:38016
}}</ref>

在WMATA的内部路线编号中，蓝线的服务经过整个J路线（从法兰克尼亚-春田站到C路线和J路线在国王街南的连接处）、部分C路线（从和J路线的连接处到地铁中心站）、部分D路线（从地铁中心站到D路线和G路线在体育场-军械库以东的连接处）和整个G路线（从和D路线体育场-军械库东的连接处到拉戈镇中心站）。<ref>Schrag at p. 188.</ref>蓝线在高峰期需要23辆六节编组列车（138个车厢）以达到运量要求。<ref>{{cite web|url = http://wmata.com/about_metro/docs/FY2009_Approved_Budget.pdf|title = Approved Fiscal 2009 Annual Budget|publisher = Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority|year = 2009|page = 80|url-status = dead|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101203023349/http://wmata.com/about_metro/docs/FY2009_Approved_Budget.pdf|archive-date = 2010-12-03}}</ref>

== “高峰+”服务 ==
2012年6月18日，华盛顿地铁开始启动已经酝酿一段时间的名为“高峰+”（{{lang-en|Rush+}}）的服务计划。该计划意在消除[[罗斯林站|罗斯林站]]的拥堵（此处蓝线和橙线交汇）且为提供[[华盛顿地铁银线|银线]]服务做好准备。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/trafficandcommuting/metro-rolls-out-rush-plus/2012/06/16/gJQA7Gw8gV_story.html|title=Blue Line split|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|last=Aratani|first=Lori|date=2012-06-06|access-date=2012-09-09|archive-date=2016-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309213904/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/trafficandcommuting/metro-rolls-out-rush-plus/2012/06/16/gJQA7Gw8gV_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>根据这一计划，蓝线保持原有线路不变，部分黄线列车从法兰克尼亚-春田站发车，经{{tsl|en|14th Street Bridge (Potomac River)|14街桥 (波多马克河)|芬威克桥}}前往[[绿带站|绿带站]]。<ref>(1) {{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2008/02/11/ST2008021102178.html |work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |date=2008-02-11 |title=Metro Explores Rerouting Blue Line |first=Lena H. |last=Sun |page=B-01 |access-date=2011-06-02 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303170047/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/story/2008/02/11/ST2008021102178.html |dead-url=no }}<br />(2) {{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/graphic/2008/02/12/GR2008021200203.html |author=Graphic |title=A New Direction for the Blue Line |date=2008-02-12 |work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |access-date=2011-06-02 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304124642/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/graphic/2008/02/12/GR2008021200203.html |dead-url=no }}<br />(3) {{cite web|url=https://www.wmata.com/about/news/pressreleasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=5186|title=Metro unveils new system map in preparation for Rush Plus: New rush service pattern begins June 18, 2012|work=Metro News Release|date=2012-03-19|publisher=Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority|quote=Rush Plus is designed to ease crowding, improve the commuting experience for Metrorail riders on the Orange, Blue, Green and Yellow lines, and prepare for the future Silver Line. .... Every third existing Blue Line train (three trains per hour in each direction) will now operate between Franconia-Springfield and Greenbelt via the Yellow Line bridge. These trains will be identified as Yellow Line trains. As a result, customers at Franconia-Springfield, Van Dorn Street and stations from L'Enfant Plaza to Greenbelt will have new transfer-free trip options between certain stations.|access-date=2021-08-27|archive-date=2017-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705201953/https://www.wmata.com/about/news/pressreleasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=5186|dead-url=no}}</ref>在高峰期，蓝线上的列车数量减少，意味着候车时间可能增加。此外，在2014年银线开通之前，一些橙线列车也驶往拉戈镇中心。<ref>(1) {{cite web|url=https://www.wmata.com/about/news/pressreleasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=5186|title=Metro unveils new system map in preparation for Rush Plus: New rush service pattern begins June 18, 2012|work=Metro News Release|date=2012-03-19|publisher=Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority|quote=Rush Plus is designed to ease crowding, improve the commuting experience for Metrorail riders on the Orange, Blue, Green and Yellow lines, and prepare for the future Silver Line. .... During each rush hour period, 18 new Orange Line trains — three per hour in each direction — will operate between Vienna and Largo Town Center.|access-date=2017-07-05|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705201953/https://www.wmata.com/about/news/pressreleasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=5186|archive-date=2017-07-05}} <br />(2) {{cite web|author=Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority|url=https://www.wmata.com/about/records/public_docs/upload/FY2015-Approved-Budget-Book.pdf|title=Gaining Momentum: FY2015 Approved Budget: Effective July 1, 2014|date=2014-05-22|access-date=2017-06-05|page=IV-33|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705195159/https://www.wmata.com/about/records/public_docs/upload/FY2015-Approved-Budget-Book.pdf|archive-date=2017-07-05}}</ref>

== 未来规划 ==
1995年11月16日，WMATA和[[亚历山德里亚_(弗吉尼亚州)|亚历山德里亚]]{{tsl|en|Potomac Yard|波多马克调车场}}区域的开发商签订了建设一个{{tsl|en|Potomac Yard (WMATA station)|波多马克场站|新车站}}的协议。车站位于{{tsl|en|Braddock Road station|布拉多克路站|布拉多克路}}和国家公园之间，由开发商出资。<ref name=History1/>{{tsl|en|Federal Transit Administration|美国联邦运输管理局}}和WMATA、[[美国国家公园管理局|国家公园管理局]]、[[亚历山德里亚_(弗吉尼亚州)|亚历山德里亚]]市政府一起，于2016年完成了该项目的{{tsl|en|environmental impact statement|环境影响报告书}}。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://potomacyardmetro.com/index.html|title=Potomac Yard Metrorail Station EIS|publisher=The Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority and the City of Alexandria|year=2016|access-date=2017-07-05|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705215803/http://potomacyardmetro.com/index.html|archive-date=2017-07-05}}</ref>预计车站将于2022年春季完工。<ref name="PostApril6">{{cite news|last1=Lazo|first1=Luz|title=Potomac Yard Metro station is over budget and behind schedule|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/dr-gridlock/wp/2018/04/06/potomac-yard-metro-station-is-over-budget-and-behind-schedule/|access-date=2018-04-06|work=The Washington Post|date=2018-04-06|archive-date=2019-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190109063244/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/dr-gridlock/wp/2018/04/06/potomac-yard-metro-station-is-over-budget-and-behind-schedule/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

第二个改进计划是兴建连接[[画廊站|画廊站]]和[[地铁中心站|地铁中心站]]的地下人行通道。2005年7月的一项研究提出将地铁中心站东侧夹层和画廊站的西侧夹层相连，它们之间仅相距一个街区。这个计划可以减少使用红线来转乘地铁中心站的黄、蓝、橙线的乘客数量。截止到2011年，该计划仍未筹集到资金。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wmata.com/about_metro/docs/PD_MCGP_Ped_Tunnel_Drawings_071405.pdf|title=Gallery Place/Chinatown – Metro Center Pedestrian Passageway|publisher=Washington Metropolitan Area Transity Authority|access-date= 2011-04-04|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110806082244/http://www.wmata.com/about_metro/docs/PD_MCGP_Ped_Tunnel_Drawings_071405.pdf|archive-date=2011-08-06}}</ref>

此外，一个运输规划组织提议延长蓝线到[[威廉王子县|威廉王子县]]的{{tsl|en|Potomac Mills, Prince William County, Virginia|波多马克磨坊 (弗吉尼亚州)|波多马克磨坊}}。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tripnet.org/state/VA/TBD_ABC7News_020811.pdf|title=Metro to Potomac Mills? Group recommends extending Blue Line, widening I-95|date=2011-02-08|publisher=WJLA-TV|location=Washington, D.C.|via=[http://www.tripnet.org tripnet.org (TRIP)]|access-date=2017-06-05|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705211439/http://www.tripnet.org/state/VA/TBD_ABC7News_020811.pdf|archive-date=2017-07-05}}</ref>

